http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Power-shutdown-tomorrow/article14025709.ece

There will be no power supply in parts of Kalaburagi city on Saturday owing to maintenance work at 110/11 kV feeder substations at Adarsh Nagar, Kalaburagi Doordarshan Kendra, Gazipur, Mehboob Nagar, Industrial Area and Taj Nagar by Gulbarga Electricity Supply Company.In a release here on Thursday, GESCOM said that several localities, including Shivaji Nagar, Aboobacker Colony, KHB Colony, Okkalgera, Bilalabad, Islamabad Colony, Qamar Colony, SBH Colony, and some areas around KBN Engineering College will go without power supply.The following areas, Syed Galli, Jalalwadi, Millat Nagar, Buland Parvez Colony, Noor Bagh, Khaja Colony, Gazipur, Milan Chowk, Kaveri Nagar, Chennamalleshwar Nagar , Majge Layout, Mahalakshmi Layout, Kailash Nagar, Manikeshwari Colony, Chowdeshwar Colony, Ganga Nagar, Lalgeri Cross, J.R. Nagar, Bale Layout, New Raghavendra Colony, Kakde Chowk, Ram Nagar, Revanasiddeshwar Colony, Chennaveer Nagar, Rajiv Gandhi Nagar, Shah Bazaar Tanda, Shiva Shakti Nagar, Nizampur, K.K. Nagar, Bhavani Nagar, and localities around Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel Chowk will also face power cut between 10 a.m. and 3 p.m. on the same day.